    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "wallet: Validate all descriptors before importing in importdescriptors",
    "user": {
      "login": "HouseOfHufflepuff",
      "id": 896651,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg5NjY1MQ==",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/896651?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/HouseOfHufflepuff",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HouseOfHufflepuff/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Extract descriptor validation into a separate `ValidateDescriptorImport()` function\r\n- Run a validation pass over all descriptors before importing any, so users get immediate error feedback without waiting for a potentially lengthy blockchain rescan\r\n- If any descriptor fails validation, return immediately — no wallet modifications or rescan are performed\r\n- Follows pinheadmz's suggested approach from #33655: \"separate the validation into a separate function entirely, so we validate in a loop first then process in a second loop\"\r\n- There's code duplication between ValidateDescriptorImport and the first half of ProcessDescriptorImport. Happy to consolidate if requested.\r\n- Addresses achow101's concern from #33874: descriptors that were not actually imported never return `success: true`\r\n\r\nfixes #33655\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] New functional test in `wallet_importdescriptors.py` verifies batch validation behavior\r\n- [x] All existing `wallet_importdescriptors.py` tests pass\r\n- [x] Unit tests pass\r\n",
